(cremating,cremated,cremates) 

1. V-T When someone is cremated , their dead body is burned, usually as part of a funeral service. 火化 [usu passive] 

例： She wants Chris to be cremated. 她想要克里斯被火化。 

2. cremation N-VAR 火化 

例： At Miss Garbo's request, there was a cremation after a private ceremony. 应加伯小姐的要求，私下举行仪式后就进行火化。

